<task id="id9YZ-09126-MT02-REZZA-Installing-ovftool"><title>Installing ovftool</title><taskbody id="d1e2717"><context>
            <p>This procedure provides instructions on how to install the ovftool required for
                deployment in VMware vCloud.</p>
            <note>
                <p>In customer lab environments, the tool must be supplied by the customer.</p>
            </note>
            <note>
                <p>For information on the ovftool, including the instruction on how to install it,
                    see VMware documentation.</p>
            </note>
            <p>To install the ovftool:</p>
        </context><steps>
<step><cmd>Login to Maestro as <codeph>spsops</codeph>. </cmd><info/></step>
<step><cmd>Switch to root by entering:</cmd><info><p>
<codeph>sudo -i</codeph>
</p></info></step>
<step><cmd>Enter:</cmd><info><p>
<codeph>$ mount -o remount,exec /tmp</codeph>
</p></info></step>
<step><cmd>Enter:</cmd><info><p>
<codeph>$ &lt;download directory&gt;/VMware-ovftool-4.4.0-5965791-lin.x86_64.bundle  -p /opt/sps/tools</codeph>
</p></info></step>
<step><cmd>Follow the instruction from the ovftool installer to complete the installation.</cmd><info/></step>
</steps>
</taskbody></task>